<section class="policy-section" id="privacy">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="policy-meta">Last Updated: See below. We will alert you about any changes via email and by updating this date.</p>
    <p>BridgeDegree ("we", "us", or "our") operates the BridgeDegree platform (the "Platform"), Nigeria's first in-school career infrastructure service that embeds employability, research visibility, and global mobility into the university journey.</p>
    <p>We are committed to protecting your privacy and handling your personal data responsibly in compliance with the Nigeria Data Protection Act 2023 (NDPA) and other applicable Nigerian laws. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, store, and protect your personal data when you access or use our website, services, or interact with us (including as students, university partners, employers, or visitors).</p>
    <p>BridgeDegree respects the privacy of its users. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our site and mobile applications. Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. <strong>IF YOU DO NOT AGREE WITH THE TERMS OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY, PLEASE DO NOT ACCESS OUR WEBSITE.</strong></p>
    <p>We reserve the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy at any time and for any reason. We will alert you about any changes via email and by updating the "Last Updated" date of this Privacy Policy. You are encouraged to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed of updates. You will be deemed to have been made aware of, will be subject to, and will be deemed to have accepted the changes in any revised Privacy Policy by your continued use of the Application after the date such revised Privacy Policy is posted.</p>

    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>We collect:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Personal identifiers (name, email, phone, student ID/matric number, date of birth, institution, course of study).</li>
      <li>Academic and career data (CV, transcripts, final-year project details, placement performance records, publication records).</li>
      <li>Professional engagement data (employer feedback, placement attendance, skill assessments).</li>
      <li>Device and usage data (IP address, browser type, pages visited, cookies-related data).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We collect this directly from you with consent/agreement, employers/partners, or automatically via cookies/technologies.</p>

    <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
    <p>We use your data to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and improve our core services (Experience Engine™, Publication Pipeline™, Global Mobility Framework™).</li>
      <li>Facilitate industry placements, research publication support, and global pathway advising.</li>
      <li>Verify experience/publications for credentials and portfolios.</li>
      <li>Communicate updates, opportunities, and platform features.</li>
      <li>Analyze usage to enhance employability outcomes.</li>
      <li>Comply with legal obligations.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Processing is based on: consent (e.g., for non-essential communications), contract performance (service delivery), legitimate interests (platform improvement), or legal obligations.</p>

    <h3>3. Sharing Your Information</h3>
    <p>We share data with:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Partner universities and institutions (for integration and outcomes tracking).</li>
      <li>Verified employers/partners (for placements and hiring pipelines, limited to necessary info).</li>
      <li>Service providers (e.g., cloud hosting, analytics tools) under strict agreements.</li>
      <li>Authorities if required by law.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell personal data. Cross-border transfers (e.g., to global journal databases or partners) include safeguards like adequacy decisions or standard contractual clauses.</p>

    <h3>4. Data Security</h3>
    <p>We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or breach (e.g., encryption, access controls). However, no system is 100% secure.</p>

    <h3>5. Your Rights Under NDPA</h3>
    <p>You have rights to: access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, object to processing, and withdraw consent (where consent-based). For children/minors (under 18), verifiable parental/guardian consent is required where applicable.</p>

    <h3>6. Data Retention</h3>
    <p>We retain data as long as necessary for service purposes, legal requirements, or dispute resolution (typically up to 7 years post-graduation for verifiable records, unless you request deletion where permissible).</p>

    <h3>7. Changes</h3>
    <p>We may update this policy; changes will be posted here with the updated date.</p>
    <p>By using BridgeDegree, you consent to this policy. Contact us for questions.</p>
  </div>
</section>

